Package validation.annotations

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    ContentType
    Annotation indicating that a field is a String indicating a content type and the validity of said String should be checked.
    ExistentOwner
    Annotation indicating that a field is the id of a User that already exists and should be validated as such.
    ExistentPost
    Annotation indicating that a field is the id of a Post that already exists and should be validated as such.
    ExistentSkillLevel
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information to identify at SkillLevel that already exists and should be validated as such.
    ExistentTag
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information to identify at Tag that already exists and should be validated as such.
    MatchedTag
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information about a Tag that should already be applied to an indicated Post and should be validated as such.
    NewSkillLevel
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information for the creation of a new SkillLevel and should be validated as such.
    NewTag
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information for creating a new Tag and should be validated as such
    NullChecks
    Annotation on a class used to perform all necessary null object/field checks before any other checks occur.
    UniqueList
    Annotation indicating that a field is a list of Tags that should all be unique.
    UnmatchedTag
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information about a Tag that should not be already applied to a particular Tag.
    UpdatedPost
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information pertaining to the update of a Post.
    UpdatedTag
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information pertaining to the update of an application of a Tag to a Post.
    UpdateExistentSkillLevel
    Annotation indicating that a class should be considered to contain information for updating a SkillLevel and should be validated accordingly.
    UpdateTag
    Annotation indicating that a class contains information for updating a Tag and should be validated as such.
    ValidTitle
    Annotation indicating that a field should be considered a Post title and checked for validity.
